        "id": 5632
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-01-25T15:09:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This looks very expensive. What is the performance like? \nHave you considered caching, if consecutive calls are likely to contain the same color?\nOr special casing common colors, if, for instance, the page is mostly white?\nHave you looked at Skia\u0027s Nx SIMD support?\npow() and exp() are very expensive -- can you do better?\n\nYou may wish to consult with experts, Brian Osman comes to mind, who\u0027ve spent a lot of time thinking about color correction and performance.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 49,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 49,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "4ac56585f37afadec9748ea7d431303119b6e965",
