    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ee534a8e_d89ca7ee",
        "filename": "src/effects/SkHighContrastFilter.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 49,
      "author": {
        "id": 6205
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-01-25T17:09:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve been trying this out in Chromium and it\u0027s actually pretty fast in practice, but of\ncourse I would like to optimize it. I was hoping to land the code first and get good\ntests and benchmarks in place, then optimize with confidence that it\u0027s not affecting\naccuracy.\n\nAny existing benchmarking code in Skia I could leverage?\n\nFor pow/exp I could use a lookup table.\n\nThe majority of the code is converting to/from HSL. There may be a\nmathematical simplification possible since I\u0027m only modifying L before\ntransforming back.\n\nVectorizing sounds good. I\u0027ve already started working on the gpu version too,\nthat seems critical.\n\nWould appreciate suggestions for reviewers / experts who could help guide me.",
      "revId": "4ac56585f37afadec9748ea7d431303119b6e965",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
